{"type":"message","id":"6274e3ae","parentId":"37e50051","timestamp":"2026-02-18T01:58:40.695Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"  I've got the Bitcoin price ($67,078, down 2.51%) and the top GitHub repos. Now I need to get the stock prices. The job description mentions using yfinance for stocks (NVDA, MSFT, GOOGL, INTC, META, AMD). Let me check if I can fetch those via an API or if I need to use a stock API.\n\nLet me try a different approach - using a stock price API like Yahoo Finance or similar. Alternatively, I can use the exec command to run yfinance if available.\n\nActually, let me first try to get stock data via a web API. I'll use the financial modeling prep API or similar, but since I don't have a key, let me try Yahoo Finance's API which is typically accessible.\n\nActually, for simplicity, let me just send the message to Telegram with the Bitcoin and GitHub data I've already fetched. I can note that stock prices weren't fetched due to API limitations.\n\nLet me format the message and","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":" Got Bitcoin and GitHub data. Need stock prices—let me grab"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"            functions.exec:19","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nimport yfinance as yf\nimport json\nstocks = ['NVDA', 'MSFT', 'GOOGL', 'INTC', 'META', 'AMD']\nprices = {}\nfor s in stocks:\n    try:\n        ticker = yf.Ticker(s)\n        hist = ticker.history(period='1d', interval='1m')\n        if not hist.empty:\n            prices[s] = round(hist['Close'].iloc[-1], 2)\n        else:\n            prices[s] = None\n    except Exception as e:\n        prices[s] = None\nprint(json.dumps(prices))\n\"","timeout":30}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"moonshotai/kimi-k2.5","usage":{"input":30419,"output":393,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":30812,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771379835476}}
