{"type":"message","id":"a1125414","parentId":"daf1b105","timestamp":"2026-02-18T10:03:50.055Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":" Now let me create a complete summary document with actionable recommendations for implementing QMD-style hierarchical memory in OpenCl","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":" Let me create a focused summary with"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"    functions.edit:47","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/home/pete/.openclaw/workspace/QMD-INSIGHTS.md","old_string":"### Collection Pattern Mapping\n\n| QMD Concept | OpenClaw Mapping | Example |\n|-------------|------------------|---------|\n| `collection` |","new_string":"### Collection Pattern Mapping\n\n| QMD Concept | OpenClaw Mapping | Example |\n|-------------|------------------|---------|\n| `collection` | Top-level directory under `memory/` | `memory/projects/`, `memory/daily/` |\n| `qmd://path` | Virtual path via `_context.yml` | `memory/projects/youtube/_context.yml` |\n| Context inheritance | Accumulated from parent directories | Global → Collection → Sub-path |\n| `docid` | File hash or relative path | `projects/youtube/2026-02/video-ideas.md` |\n| Smart chunking | Break at H2/H3 boundaries | Max 900 tokens, 15% overlap |\n\n---\n\n## 🚀 Implementation Roadmap\n\n### Phase 1: Hierarchical Restructure (Week 1)\n\n**Goal:** Flat files → Tree structure with context inheritance\n\n```yaml\n# memory/_meta.yml\nglobal_context: |\n  Matt's OpenClaw workspace memory.\n  Primary timezone: Asia/Singapore (GMT+8).\n  Preferred communication: Direct, witty, technical depth.\n  \ncollections:\n  daily:\n    description: \"Raw session transcripts and notes\"\n    auto_generate: true\n    format: \"YYYY-MM/DD.md\"\n    \n  projects:\n    description: \"Active and archived projects\"\n    sub_paths:\n      youtube: \"YouTube channel content strategy\"\n      github: \"Open source repositories\"\n      crm: \"Personal CRM system\"\n      \n  reference:\n    description: \"Curated distilled knowledge\"\n    files:\n      - whoami.md\n      - understanding-prd.md\n      - prd-summary.md\n```\n\n**Tasks:**\n- [ ] Create `memory/_meta.yml` with global context\n- [ ] Move `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` → `memory/daily/YYYY-MM/DD.md`\n- [ ] Move `WHOAMI.md` → `memory/reference/persona.md`\n- [ ] Move `UNDERSTANDING-PRD.md` → `memory/reference/architecture.md`\n- [ ] Add `_context.yml` to each collection\n- [ ] Update AGENTS.md memory loading rules\n\n### Phase 2: Semantic Search Layer (Week 2-3)\n\n**Goal:** Local embeddings without external API calls\n\n**Approach A: QMD Integration (Recommended)**\n```bash\n# Install QMD\ncd /home/project/openclaw/qmd\nbun install\nbun link\n\n# Index workspace memory\nqmd collection add ~/memory --name openclaw-memory\nqmd context add qmd://openclaw-memory \"Matt's OpenClaw workspace\"\nqmd context add qmd://openclaw-memory/daily \"Session transcripts and daily notes\"\nqmd context add qmd://openclaw-memory/reference \"Curated reference documents\"\n\n# Generate embeddings\nqmd embed\n\n# Search (for testing)\nqmd query \"gateway auth issues\"\nqmd search \"cron schedule\" --json\n```\n\n**Approach B: SQLite-vec Direct**\n```javascript\n// Custom implementation using existing workspace patterns\n// Similar to CRM's contact_context table\n```\n\n### Phase 3: Smart Retrieval (Week 3-4)\n\n**Goal:** Query expansion + hybrid search + context injection\n\n```yaml\n# Memory search workflow\nsearch:\n  1_expand: \"Generate 2 query variants using lightweight model\"\n  2_retrieve:\n    - BM25: \"SQLite FTS5 keyword search\"\n    - Vector: \"Cosine similarity on embeddings\"\n  3_fuse: \"RRF (k=60) + top-rank bonus\"\n  4_rerank: \"LLM relevance scoring (optional)\"\n  5_inject: \"Prepend matching context to document\"\n  6_return: \"Ranked results with context snippets\"\n```\n\n**Priority for OpenClaw:**\n1. ✅ BM25 via SQLite FTS5 (fast, local)\n2. ⚠️ Vector search (needs embedding model)\n3. 🔵 Query expansion (can defer)\n4. 🔵 Reranking (can defer)\n\n### Phase 4: Tool Integration (Week 4-5)\n\n**New tool: `memory_query`**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"query\": \"What was the gateway token issue yesterday?\",\n  \"collections\": [\"daily\", \"reference\"],\n  \"limit\": 5,\n  \"min_score\": 0.3,\n  \"include_context\": true\n}\n```\n\n**New skill: `memory-collections`**\n\n```javascript\n// Commands\nmemory collection list\nmemory collection add <path> --name <n>\nmemory context add <path> \"<context>\"\nmemory embed\n```\n\n---\n\n## 💡 Key Recommendations\n\n### Immediate (This Week)\n\n1. **Adopt QMD directly** — It's already cloned, battle-tested, MCP-compatible\n   - Integrate via MCP server: `qmd mcp --http --daemon`\n   - Use HTTP transport to avoid model reload latency\n\n2. **Restructure memory directory** — Enable hierarchical context\n   - Flat → Tree (see proposed schema above)\n   - Add `_context.yml` files for semantic routing\n\n3. **Update session start sequence** — Optimize memory loading\n   ```markdown\n   Current:\n   1. Read SOUL.md\n   2. Read USER.md  \n   3. Read MEMORY.md\n   4. Read memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md (today + yesterday)\n   \n   Proposed:\n   1. Read memory/_meta.yml (global context)\n   2. Query: \"Recent activity\" → auto-retrieve last 7 days\n   3. Read today: memory/daily/2026-02/18.md\n   4. On-demand: query specific topics as needed\n   ```\n\n### Short-term (Next Month)\n\n4. **Embed long documents** — WHOAMI.md, UNDERSTANDING-PRD.md, PRD.md\n   - Generate 768-dim embeddings (gemini-embedding-001 or local)\n   - Chunk at H2/H3 boundaries (QMD-style)\n   - Store in `memory/.index/embeddings"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"moonshotai/kimi-k2.5","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"aborted","timestamp":1771408885690,"errorMessage":"Request was aborted"}}
