{"type":"message","id":"aed53ce8","parentId":"75443e88","timestamp":"2026-02-19T01:49:46.999Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"206\",\n  \"sender\": \"1087368827\"\n}\n```\n\nyou should use the python script already created. check the past history. $ ls -lt /home/project/openclaw/*py /home/project/openclaw/*sh -rw-rw-r-- 1 pete pete 13370 Feb 3 09:02 /home/project/openclaw/extract_design_playwright.py -rwxrwxr-x 1 pete pete 6382 Feb 3 08:47 /home/project/openclaw/test-design-extraction.sh -rwxrwxr-x 1 pete pete 3783 Feb 3 08:03 /home/project/openclaw/daily-ping-cron.sh -rw-rw-r-- 1 pete pete 637 Feb 3 07:58 /home/project/openclaw/design_extraction_with_retry.sh -rwxrwxr-x 1 pete pete 1763 Feb 2 20:32 /home/project/openclaw/heartbeat-spx-monitor.sh -rw-rw-r-- 1 pete pete 13203 Feb 2 20:31 /home/project/openclaw/spx_monitor_v3.py -rw-rw-r-- 1 pete pete 17375 Feb 2 20:16 /home/project/openclaw/spx_monitor.py -rwxrwxr-x 1 pete pete 1031 Feb 2 16:28 /home/project/openclaw/generate-daily-message.sh -rwxrwxr-x 1 pete pete 1087 Feb 2 16:16 /home/project/openclaw/format-and-send-daily-ping.sh -rwxrwxr-x 1 pete pete 4442 Feb 2 15:46 /home/project/openclaw/daily-ping-sender.py also instead of *Top 5 GitHub Repos by Stars*, I prefer top 10 *trending* projects on GitHub"}],"timestamp":1771465786989}}
{"type":"message","id":"af212c2c","parentId":"aed53ce8","timestamp":"2026-02-19T01:50:36.626Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":" The user wants me to use existing Python scripts for the daily ping, and also change from \"Top 5 GitHub Repos by Stars\" to \"Top 10 trending projects on GitHub\". Let me","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":" functions.read:80","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/project/openclaw/daily-ping-sender.py"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":" functions.read:81","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/project/openclaw/daily-ping-cron.sh"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":" functions.read:82","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/project/openclaw/generate-daily-message.sh"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"moonshotai/kimi-k2.5","usage":{"input":120052,"output":125,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":120177,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771465786995}}
{"type":"message","id":"d93d69b5","parentId":"af212c2c","timestamp":"2026-02-19T01:50:36.641Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":" functions.read:80","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"\nDaily Ping Message Sender\nReads data from cron job logs and sends formatted message via Telegram\n\"\"\"\n\nimport json\nimport re\nfrom datetime import datetime\nimport subprocess\nimport sys\n\ndef read_log_file():\n    \"\"\"Read today's log file\"\"\"\n    today = datetime.now().strftime(\"%Y-%m-%d\")\n    log_file = f\"/home/project/openclaw/logs/daily-ping-{today}.log\"\n    \n    try:\n        with open(log_file, 'r') as f:\n            return f.read()\n    except FileNotFoundError:\n        return None\n\ndef parse_bitcoin_data(log_content):\n    \"\"\"Extract Bitcoin price and change from log\"\"\"\n    match = re.search(r'Bitcoin: (\\d+) \\(change: ([-\\d.]+)%\\)', log_content)\n    if match:\n        return {\n            'price': int(match.group(1)),\n            'change': float(match.group(2))\n        }\n    return None\n\ndef parse_stock_data(log_content):\n    \"\"\"Extract stock data from log\"\"\"\n    # Look for JSON block in log\n    json_match = re.search(r'\\{[^{}]*\"NVDA\"[^{}]*\\}', log_content, re.DOTALL)\n    if json_match:\n        try:\n            return json.loads(json_match.group())\n        except:\n            pass\n    return None\n\ndef format_message(bitcoin, stocks):\n    \"\"\"Format the daily ping message\"\"\"\n    date_str = datetime.now().strftime(\"%A, %B %d, %Y\")\n    \n    # Bitcoin section\n    btc_emoji = \"🔻\" if bitcoin['change'] < 0 else \"🟢\"\n    btc_alert = \"⚠️ ALERT: Drop > 10%!\" if bitcoin['change'] < -10 else \"✅ No alert\"\n    \n    message = f\"\"\"📅 **Daily Ping — {date_str}**\n\n💰 **Bitcoin Price**\n• Current: **${bitcoin['price']:,} USD**\n• 24h Change: **{bitcoin['change']:+.2f}%** {btc_emoji}\n• Status: {btc_alert}\n\n📊 **Tech Stocks (24h Change)**\n\n\"\"\"\n    \n    # Stock table\n    if stocks:\n        for symbol, data in stocks.items():\n            if 'error' not in data:\n                emoji = \"🔴\" if data['change_pct'] < 0 else \"🟢\"\n                company = data.get('company', symbol)\n                message += f\"• **{company}** ({symbol}): ${data['price']:.2f} ({data['change_pct']:+.2f}%) {emoji}\\n\"\n        \n        # Market summary\n        down_count = sum(1 for s in stocks.values() if 'error' not in s and s['change_pct'] < 0)\n        total_count = sum(1 for s in stocks.values() if 'error' not in s)\n        \n        message += f\"\\n📈 **Market Summary:** {down_count} of {total_count} stocks down\"\n        \n        # Find biggest loser\n        biggest_loser = None\n        biggest_drop = 0\n        for symbol, data in stocks.items():\n            if 'error' not in data and data['change_pct'] < biggest_drop:\n                biggest_drop = data['change_pct']\n                biggest_loser = symbol\n        \n        if biggest_loser:\n            message += f\" | 🔥 **{biggest_loser}** hit hardest at {biggest_drop:.2f}%\"\n    \n    message += \"\"\"\n\n🚀 **GitHub Top Repositories**\n✅ Top 5 trending repositories fetched\n\n---\n*Have a productive day!* 🤝\n\"\"\"\n    \n    return message\n\ndef send_telegram_message(message):\n    \"\"\"Send message via Telegram using OpenClaw\"\"\"\n    # Use OpenClaw CLI to send message\n    cmd = [\n        \"openclaw\", \"message\", \"send\",\n        \"--target\", \"1087368827\",\n        \"--channel\", \"telegram\",\n        \"--text\", message\n    ]\n    \n    try:\n        result = subprocess.run(cmd, capture_output=True, text=True)\n        return result.returncode == 0\n    except Exception as e:\n        print(f\"Error sending message: {e}\")\n        return False\n\ndef main():\n    \"\"\"Main function\"\"\"\n    log_content = read_log_file()\n    \n    if not log_content:\n        print(\"Error: No log file found for today\")\n        sys.exit(1)\n    \n    bitcoin = parse_bitcoin_data(log_content)\n    stocks = parse_stock_data(log_content)\n    \n    if not bitcoin:\n        print(\"Error: Could not parse Bitcoin data\")\n        sys.exit(1)\n    \n    message = format_message(bitcoin, stocks)\n    \n    # Save formatted message for debugging\n    today = datetime.now().strftime(\"%Y-%m-%d\")\n    with open(f\"/home/project/openclaw/logs/message-{today}.txt\", 'w') as f:\n        f.write(message)\n    \n    print(\"Formatted message:\")\n    print(message)\n    print(\"\\n\" + \"=\"*50)\n    print(\"To send via Telegram, run with --send flag\")\n    \n    if \"--send\" in sys.argv:\n        if send_telegram_message(message):\n            print(\"✅ Message sent successfully!\")\n        else:\n            print(\"❌ Failed to send message\")\n            sys.exit(1)\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    main()\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1771465836638}}
{"type":"message","id":"4b65e531","parentId":"d93d69b5","timestamp":"2026-02-19T01:50:36.650Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":" functions.read:81","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/bin/bash\n# Daily Ping Cron Job v2.0\n# Executes at 7:00 AM SGT (23:00 UTC)\n# Fixed: Better error handling, PATH setup for cron, explicit logging\n\n# Set PATH for cron environment\nexport PATH=\"/usr/local/bin:/usr/bin:/bin:/opt/venv/bin:$PATH\"\n\n# Log file setup\nLOG_DIR=\"/home/project/openclaw/logs\"\nLOG_FILE=\"$LOG_DIR/daily-ping-$(date +%Y-%m-%d).log\"\n\n# Ensure log directory exists\nif ! mkdir -p \"$LOG_DIR\" 2>/dev/null; then\n    echo \"ERROR: Cannot create log directory $LOG_DIR\" >&2\n    exit 1\nfi\n\n# Check if we can write to log file\nif ! touch \"$LOG_FILE\" 2>/dev/null; then\n    echo \"ERROR: Cannot write to log file $LOG_FILE\" >&2\n    exit 1\nfi\n\n# Function to log with timestamp\nlog() {\n    echo \"[$(date '+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S %Z')] $1\" >> \"$LOG_FILE\"\n}\n\nlog \"Starting daily ping job...\"\nlog \"Log file: $LOG_FILE\"\n\n# Fetch Bitcoin price from CoinGecko\nlog \"Fetching Bitcoin data from CoinGecko...\"\nBTC_DATA=$(curl -s --max-time 30 \"https://api.coingecko.com/api/v3/simple/price?ids=bitcoin&vs_currencies=usd&include_24hr_change=true\" 2>&1)\nCURL_EXIT=$?\n\nif [ $CURL_EXIT -ne 0 ]; then\n    log \"ERROR: Bitcoin fetch failed (curl exit: $CURL_EXIT)\"\n    log \"Curl output: $BTC_DATA\"\nelse\n    BTC_PRICE=$(echo \"$BTC_DATA\" | grep -o '\"usd\":[0-9]*' | head -1 | cut -d: -f2)\n    BTC_CHANGE=$(echo \"$BTC_DATA\" | grep -o '\"usd_24h_change\":[-0-9.]*' | head -1 | cut -d: -f2)\n    \n    if [ -z \"$BTC_PRICE\" ]; then\n        log \"ERROR: Could not parse Bitcoin price from response\"\n        log \"Response: $BTC_DATA\"\n    else\n        log \"Bitcoin: $BTC_PRICE (change: $BTC_CHANGE%)\"\n    fi\nfi\n\n# Fetch top GitHub repos\nlog \"Fetching GitHub data...\"\nGH_DATA=$(curl -s --max-time 30 \"https://api.github.com/search/repositories?q=stars:>1000&sort=stars&order=desc&per_page=5\" 2>&1)\nCURL_EXIT=$?\n\nif [ $CURL_EXIT -ne 0 ]; then\n    log \"ERROR: GitHub fetch failed (curl exit: $CURL_EXIT)\"\nelse\n    # Verify we got valid JSON\n    if echo \"$GH_DATA\" | grep -q '\"total_count\":'; then\n        log \"GitHub data fetched successfully\"\n    else\n        log \"ERROR: GitHub response invalid\"\n        log \"Response preview: $(echo \"$GH_DATA\" | head -c 200)\"\n    fi\nfi\n\n# Fetch stock data using uv run (more reliable than source activate)\nlog \"Fetching stock data (NVDA, MSFT, GOOGL, INTC, META, AMD)...\"\n\n# Use uv run from the correct directory\ncd /home/project/openclaw || exit 1\n\nSTOCK_OUTPUT=$(uv run python3 << 'PYTHON_SCRIPT'\nimport yfinance as yf\nimport json\nimport sys\n\ntickers = ['NVDA', 'MSFT', 'GOOGL', 'INTC', 'META', 'AMD']\nresults = {}\n\ntry:\n    for symbol in tickers:\n        try:\n            t = yf.Ticker(symbol)\n            info = t.info\n            current_price = info.get('currentPrice') or info.get('regularMarketPrice', 0)\n            prev_close = info.get('previousClose', 0)\n            change_pct = info.get('regularMarketChangePercent')\n            if change_pct is None and prev_close > 0:\n                change_pct = ((current_price - prev_close) / prev_close) * 100\n            results[symbol] = {\n                'price': current_price,\n                'change_pct': change_pct or 0,\n                'company': info.get('shortName', symbol)\n            }\n        except Exception as e:\n            results[symbol] = {'error': str(e)}\n    \n    print(json.dumps(results))\n    sys.exit(0)\nexcept Exception as e:\n    print(json.dumps({'error': str(e)}))\n    sys.exit(1)\nPYTHON_SCRIPT\n2>&1)\n\nPYTHON_EXIT=$?\n\nif [ $PYTHON_EXIT -ne 0 ]; then\n    log \"ERROR: Stock data fetch failed (python exit: $PYTHON_EXIT)\"\n    log \"Python output: $STOCK_OUTPUT\"\nelse\n    echo \"$STOCK_OUTPUT\" >> \"$LOG_FILE\"\n    log \"Stock data fetched successfully\"\nfi\n\nlog \"Daily ping job completed\"\n\n# Return appropriate exit code\nif [ $CURL_EXIT -ne 0 ] || [ $PYTHON_EXIT -ne 0 ]; then\n    exit 1\nelse\n    exit 0\nfi\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1771465836645}}
{"type":"message","id":"76ddbbe1","parentId":"4b65e531","timestamp":"2026-02-19T01:50:36.662Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":" functions.read:82","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/bin/bash\n# Generate Daily Ping Message File\n# This script reads the log and creates a formatted message file\n\nLOG_FILE=\"/home/project/openclaw/logs/daily-ping-$(date +%Y-%m-%d).log\"\nMESSAGE_FILE=\"/home/project/openclaw/daily-message.txt\"\n\n# Check if log exists\nif [ ! -f \"$LOG_FILE\" ]; then\n    echo \"Error: Log file not found\" >&2\n    exit 1\nfi\n\n# Extract data from log\nBTC_PRICE=$(grep -o '\"usd\":[0-9]*' \"$LOG_FILE\" | tail -1 | cut -d: -f2)\nBTC_CHANGE=$(grep -o '\"usd_24h_change\":[-0-9.]*' \"$LOG_FILE\" | tail -1 | cut -d: -f2)\n\n# Format change with sign\nif (( $(echo \"$BTC_CHANGE > 0\" | bc -l) )); then\n    BTC_TREND=\"📈\"\nelse\n    BTC_TREND=\"📉\"\nfi\n\n# Create message\ncat > \"$MESSAGE_FILE\" << EOF\n📅 Daily Ping — $(date +\"%A, %B %d, %Y\")\n\n💰 Bitcoin Price\n• Current: \\$${BTC_PRICE} USD\n• 24h Change: ${BTC_CHANGE}% ${BTC_TREND}\n\n📊 Tech Stocks data available in log file\n🚀 GitHub repositories data available in log file\n\n📈 Summary: Data collected successfully\nEOF\n\necho \"Message generated: $MESSAGE_FILE\"\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1771465836656}}
