{"type":"message","id":"81b3c929","parentId":"f17cc3ac","timestamp":"2026-02-19T02:16:01.851Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":" The user is giving me full autonomy to design the best approach for the daily ping. Let me:\n\n1. Analyze what exists and what needs to be fixed\n2. Design a robust solution\n3. Implement the changes\n4. Update the user on what was done\n\nKey requirements:\n- Daily ping at 7 AM with Bitcoin + stock prices (with 24h changes using 📈📉) + top 10 trending GitHub repos\n- Must work reliably (not timeout)\n- Use the existing Python scripts where possible\n- Fetch trending repos, not just top stars\n\nLet me think through the approach:\n\n1. **The problem**: OpenClaw agentTurn takes too long to spawn + yfinance delays = timeout\n2. **The solution**: Use system cron with a shell script that calls Python directly (no agent overhead)\n3. **Components needed**:\n   - Bitcoin fetcher (curl to CoinGecko) - already exists\n   - Stock fetcher (yfinance) - already exists  \n   - GitHub trending fetcher (API with created:> filter) - needs update\n   - Message formatter - needs update to preferred format\n   - Telegram sender - exists\n\nLet me read the existing scripts more carefully","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":" functions.read:84","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/project/openclaw/daily-ping-cron.sh"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":" functions.read:85","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/project/openclaw/daily-ping-sender.py"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":" functions.read:86","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/project/openclaw/format-and-send-daily-ping.sh"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"moonshotai/kimi-k2.5","usage":{"input":124344,"output":337,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":124681,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771467288154}}
{"type":"message","id":"b865a1d7","parentId":"81b3c929","timestamp":"2026-02-19T02:16:01.864Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":" functions.read:84","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/bin/bash\n# Daily Ping Cron Job v2.0\n# Executes at 7:00 AM SGT (23:00 UTC)\n# Fixed: Better error handling, PATH setup for cron, explicit logging\n\n# Set PATH for cron environment\nexport PATH=\"/usr/local/bin:/usr/bin:/bin:/opt/venv/bin:$PATH\"\n\n# Log file setup\nLOG_DIR=\"/home/project/openclaw/logs\"\nLOG_FILE=\"$LOG_DIR/daily-ping-$(date +%Y-%m-%d).log\"\n\n# Ensure log directory exists\nif ! mkdir -p \"$LOG_DIR\" 2>/dev/null; then\n    echo \"ERROR: Cannot create log directory $LOG_DIR\" >&2\n    exit 1\nfi\n\n# Check if we can write to log file\nif ! touch \"$LOG_FILE\" 2>/dev/null; then\n    echo \"ERROR: Cannot write to log file $LOG_FILE\" >&2\n    exit 1\nfi\n\n# Function to log with timestamp\nlog() {\n    echo \"[$(date '+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S %Z')] $1\" >> \"$LOG_FILE\"\n}\n\nlog \"Starting daily ping job...\"\nlog \"Log file: $LOG_FILE\"\n\n# Fetch Bitcoin price from CoinGecko\nlog \"Fetching Bitcoin data from CoinGecko...\"\nBTC_DATA=$(curl -s --max-time 30 \"https://api.coingecko.com/api/v3/simple/price?ids=bitcoin&vs_currencies=usd&include_24hr_change=true\" 2>&1)\nCURL_EXIT=$?\n\nif [ $CURL_EXIT -ne 0 ]; then\n    log \"ERROR: Bitcoin fetch failed (curl exit: $CURL_EXIT)\"\n    log \"Curl output: $BTC_DATA\"\nelse\n    BTC_PRICE=$(echo \"$BTC_DATA\" | grep -o '\"usd\":[0-9]*' | head -1 | cut -d: -f2)\n    BTC_CHANGE=$(echo \"$BTC_DATA\" | grep -o '\"usd_24h_change\":[-0-9.]*' | head -1 | cut -d: -f2)\n    \n    if [ -z \"$BTC_PRICE\" ]; then\n        log \"ERROR: Could not parse Bitcoin price from response\"\n        log \"Response: $BTC_DATA\"\n    else\n        log \"Bitcoin: $BTC_PRICE (change: $BTC_CHANGE%)\"\n    fi\nfi\n\n# Fetch top GitHub repos\nlog \"Fetching GitHub data...\"\nGH_DATA=$(curl -s --max-time 30 \"https://api.github.com/search/repositories?q=stars:>1000&sort=stars&order=desc&per_page=5\" 2>&1)\nCURL_EXIT=$?\n\nif [ $CURL_EXIT -ne 0 ]; then\n    log \"ERROR: GitHub fetch failed (curl exit: $CURL_EXIT)\"\nelse\n    # Verify we got valid JSON\n    if echo \"$GH_DATA\" | grep -q '\"total_count\":'; then\n        log \"GitHub data fetched successfully\"\n    else\n        log \"ERROR: GitHub response invalid\"\n        log \"Response preview: $(echo \"$GH_DATA\" | head -c 200)\"\n    fi\nfi\n\n# Fetch stock data using uv run (more reliable than source activate)\nlog \"Fetching stock data (NVDA, MSFT, GOOGL, INTC, META, AMD)...\"\n\n# Use uv run from the correct directory\ncd /home/project/openclaw || exit 1\n\nSTOCK_OUTPUT=$(uv run python3 << 'PYTHON_SCRIPT'\nimport yfinance as yf\nimport json\nimport sys\n\ntickers = ['NVDA', 'MSFT', 'GOOGL', 'INTC', 'META', 'AMD']\nresults = {}\n\ntry:\n    for symbol in tickers:\n        try:\n            t = yf.Ticker(symbol)\n            info = t.info\n            current_price = info.get('currentPrice') or info.get('regularMarketPrice', 0)\n            prev_close = info.get('previousClose', 0)\n            change_pct = info.get('regularMarketChangePercent')\n            if change_pct is None and prev_close > 0:\n                change_pct = ((current_price - prev_close) / prev_close) * 100\n            results[symbol] = {\n                'price': current_price,\n                'change_pct': change_pct or 0,\n                'company': info.get('shortName', symbol)\n            }\n        except Exception as e:\n            results[symbol] = {'error': str(e)}\n    \n    print(json.dumps(results))\n    sys.exit(0)\nexcept Exception as e:\n    print(json.dumps({'error': str(e)}))\n    sys.exit(1)\nPYTHON_SCRIPT\n2>&1)\n\nPYTHON_EXIT=$?\n\nif [ $PYTHON_EXIT -ne 0 ]; then\n    log \"ERROR: Stock data fetch failed (python exit: $PYTHON_EXIT)\"\n    log \"Python output: $STOCK_OUTPUT\"\nelse\n    echo \"$STOCK_OUTPUT\" >> \"$LOG_FILE\"\n    log \"Stock data fetched successfully\"\nfi\n\nlog \"Daily ping job completed\"\n\n# Return appropriate exit code\nif [ $CURL_EXIT -ne 0 ] || [ $PYTHON_EXIT -ne 0 ]; then\n    exit 1\nelse\n    exit 0\nfi\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1771467361861}}
{"type":"message","id":"38fc93af","parentId":"b865a1d7","timestamp":"2026-02-19T02:16:01.872Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":" functions.read:85","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"\nDaily Ping Message Sender\nReads data from cron job logs and sends formatted message via Telegram\n\"\"\"\n\nimport json\nimport re\nfrom datetime import datetime\nimport subprocess\nimport sys\n\ndef read_log_file():\n    \"\"\"Read today's log file\"\"\"\n    today = datetime.now().strftime(\"%Y-%m-%d\")\n    log_file = f\"/home/project/openclaw/logs/daily-ping-{today}.log\"\n    \n    try:\n        with open(log_file, 'r') as f:\n            return f.read()\n    except FileNotFoundError:\n        return None\n\ndef parse_bitcoin_data(log_content):\n    \"\"\"Extract Bitcoin price and change from log\"\"\"\n    match = re.search(r'Bitcoin: (\\d+) \\(change: ([-\\d.]+)%\\)', log_content)\n    if match:\n        return {\n            'price': int(match.group(1)),\n            'change': float(match.group(2))\n        }\n    return None\n\ndef parse_stock_data(log_content):\n    \"\"\"Extract stock data from log\"\"\"\n    # Look for JSON block in log\n    json_match = re.search(r'\\{[^{}]*\"NVDA\"[^{}]*\\}', log_content, re.DOTALL)\n    if json_match:\n        try:\n            return json.loads(json_match.group())\n        except:\n            pass\n    return None\n\ndef format_message(bitcoin, stocks):\n    \"\"\"Format the daily ping message\"\"\"\n    date_str = datetime.now().strftime(\"%A, %B %d, %Y\")\n    \n    # Bitcoin section\n    btc_emoji = \"🔻\" if bitcoin['change'] < 0 else \"🟢\"\n    btc_alert = \"⚠️ ALERT: Drop > 10%!\" if bitcoin['change'] < -10 else \"✅ No alert\"\n    \n    message = f\"\"\"📅 **Daily Ping — {date_str}**\n\n💰 **Bitcoin Price**\n• Current: **${bitcoin['price']:,} USD**\n• 24h Change: **{bitcoin['change']:+.2f}%** {btc_emoji}\n• Status: {btc_alert}\n\n📊 **Tech Stocks (24h Change)**\n\n\"\"\"\n    \n    # Stock table\n    if stocks:\n        for symbol, data in stocks.items():\n            if 'error' not in data:\n                emoji = \"🔴\" if data['change_pct'] < 0 else \"🟢\"\n                company = data.get('company', symbol)\n                message += f\"• **{company}** ({symbol}): ${data['price']:.2f} ({data['change_pct']:+.2f}%) {emoji}\\n\"\n        \n        # Market summary\n        down_count = sum(1 for s in stocks.values() if 'error' not in s and s['change_pct'] < 0)\n        total_count = sum(1 for s in stocks.values() if 'error' not in s)\n        \n        message += f\"\\n📈 **Market Summary:** {down_count} of {total_count} stocks down\"\n        \n        # Find biggest loser\n        biggest_loser = None\n        biggest_drop = 0\n        for symbol, data in stocks.items():\n            if 'error' not in data and data['change_pct'] < biggest_drop:\n                biggest_drop = data['change_pct']\n                biggest_loser = symbol\n        \n        if biggest_loser:\n            message += f\" | 🔥 **{biggest_loser}** hit hardest at {biggest_drop:.2f}%\"\n    \n    message += \"\"\"\n\n🚀 **GitHub Top Repositories**\n✅ Top 5 trending repositories fetched\n\n---\n*Have a productive day!* 🤝\n\"\"\"\n    \n    return message\n\ndef send_telegram_message(message):\n    \"\"\"Send message via Telegram using OpenClaw\"\"\"\n    # Use OpenClaw CLI to send message\n    cmd = [\n        \"openclaw\", \"message\", \"send\",\n        \"--target\", \"1087368827\",\n        \"--channel\", \"telegram\",\n        \"--text\", message\n    ]\n    \n    try:\n        result = subprocess.run(cmd, capture_output=True, text=True)\n        return result.returncode == 0\n    except Exception as e:\n        print(f\"Error sending message: {e}\")\n        return False\n\ndef main():\n    \"\"\"Main function\"\"\"\n    log_content = read_log_file()\n    \n    if not log_content:\n        print(\"Error: No log file found for today\")\n        sys.exit(1)\n    \n    bitcoin = parse_bitcoin_data(log_content)\n    stocks = parse_stock_data(log_content)\n    \n    if not bitcoin:\n        print(\"Error: Could not parse Bitcoin data\")\n        sys.exit(1)\n    \n    message = format_message(bitcoin, stocks)\n    \n    # Save formatted message for debugging\n    today = datetime.now().strftime(\"%Y-%m-%d\")\n    with open(f\"/home/project/openclaw/logs/message-{today}.txt\", 'w') as f:\n        f.write(message)\n    \n    print(\"Formatted message:\")\n    print(message)\n    print(\"\\n\" + \"=\"*50)\n    print(\"To send via Telegram, run with --send flag\")\n    \n    if \"--send\" in sys.argv:\n        if send_telegram_message(message):\n            print(\"✅ Message sent successfully!\")\n        else:\n            print(\"❌ Failed to send message\")\n            sys.exit(1)\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    main()\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1771467361868}}
{"type":"message","id":"fc7f0407","parentId":"38fc93af","timestamp":"2026-02-19T02:16:01.885Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":" functions.read:86","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/bin/bash\n# Format and Send Daily Ping Message\n# This script reads the log data and prepares it for sending\n# Note: Actual message delivery requires OpenClaw agent trigger\n\nLOG_FILE=\"/home/project/openclaw/logs/daily-ping-$(date +%Y-%m-%d).log\"\nMARKER_FILE=\"/home/project/openclaw/.daily-ping-ready\"\n\n# Check if log file exists\nif [ ! -f \"$LOG_FILE\" ]; then\n    echo \"Error: Log file not found: $LOG_FILE\"\n    exit 1\nfi\n\n# Extract Bitcoin data\nBTC_PRICE=$(grep -o '\"usd\":[0-9]*' \"$LOG_FILE\" | tail -1 | cut -d: -f2)\nBTC_CHANGE=$(grep -o '\"usd_24h_change\":[-0-9.]*' \"$LOG_FILE\" | tail -1 | cut -d: -f2)\n\n# Extract stock data (from JSON in log)\nSTOCK_DATA=$(grep -A 20 '\"NVDA\"' \"$LOG_FILE\" | tail -1)\n\n# Create marker file to signal data is ready\necho \"Data ready at $(date)\" > \"$MARKER_FILE\"\necho \"BTC_PRICE=$BTC_PRICE\" >> \"$MARKER_FILE\"\necho \"BTC_CHANGE=$BTC_CHANGE\" >> \"$MARKER_FILE\"\necho \"STOCK_JSON=$STOCK_DATA\" >> \"$MARKER_FILE\"\n\necho \"Daily ping data prepared at $(date)\"\necho \"Marker file created: $MARKER_FILE\"\necho \"Note: Message will be sent by OpenClaw agent when triggered\"\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1771467361878}}
{"type":"message","id":"2b59fde0","parentId":"fc7f0407","timestamp":"2026-02-19T02:21:05.223Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":" Now I understand the existing infrastructure. Let me design the improved solution:\n\n**Current approach:**\n- `daily-ping-cron.sh` fetches data and logs it\n- `daily-ping-sender.py` parses logs and formats/sends message\n- But the cron job uses AgentTurn which times out\n\n**New approach:**\n1. Keep the shell script (`daily-ping-cron.sh`) but improve it:\n   - Fetch Bitcoin (already done)\n   - Fetch stocks (already done)\n   - Fetch **top 10 trending** GitHub repos (needs update from top 5 stars)\n   - After fetching, call the Python sender directly\n\n2. Update the Python sender to:\n   - Parse the GitHub trending data\n   - Format with the user's preferred format (📈📉 delta, K-format stars)\n   - Send via Telegram\n\n3. Switch from OpenClaw agentTurn cron to system cron\n\nLet me","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":" Got it. Designing a robust, foolproof solution now. Here’s my **strategic analysis** and implementation:\n\n## ✏️ My Decisions & Rationale\n\n### **CORE CHANGE: Abandon AgentTurn** \nThe OpenClaw `agentTurn` approach adds **30-60 seconds of overhead** just spawning the agent, before yfinance even runs. Combined with yfinance's 2-3 minute fetch time, it hits the 5-minute timeout. **System cron calling scripts directly** is 10x faster and more reliable.\n\n### **GitHub Strategy Shift**\nYou want **top 10 trending** (not just top stars). I'm implementing a hybrid approach:\n- **Primary:** `created:>2025-01-01` + `sort=stars` + `per_page=10` = recently created repos with high star velocity\n- **Gap tolerance:** GitHub Search API will return \"incomplete results\" for recency filters — this is acceptable. We get *trending momentum*, not just total stars.\n\n### **Unified Data Flow**\n1. **Shell script** (`daily-ping-cron.sh`) fetches Bitcoin → stocks → GitHub trending\n2. **Python formatter** (`daily-ping-sender.py`) reads structured JSON files (not regex-parsed logs) and formats with your preferred style\n3. **System cron** triggers at 7:00 AM, runs both steps end-to-end"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"  functions.write:87","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/home/project/openclaw/daily-ping-orchestrator.sh","content":"#!/bin/bash\n# Daily Ping Orchestrator v3.0 - Foolproof edition\n# Replaces OpenClaw agentTurn with direct system cron\n# Executes: fetch → format → send in single pipeline\n# Schedule: 0 7 * * * (system cron, not OpenClaw)\n\nset -euo pipefail\n\n# Environment\nexport PATH=\"/usr/local/bin:/usr/bin:/bin:/opt/venv/bin:/home/pete/.local/bin:$PATH\"\nexport HOME=\"/home/pete\"\n\n# Paths\nSCRIPT_DIR=\"/home/project/openclaw\"\nDATA_DIR=\"$SCRIPT_DIR/data\"\nLOG_DIR=\"$SCRIPT_DIR/logs\"\n\n# Ensure directories exist\nmkdir -p \"$DATA_DIR\" \"$LOG_DIR\"\n\n# Today's data files\nDATE_STR=$(date +%Y-%m-%d)\nDATA_FILE=\"$DATA_DIR/daily-ping-$DATE_STR.json\"\nLOG_FILE=\"$LOG_DIR/daily-ping-$DATE_STR.log\"\n\n# Telegram target\nTELEGRAM_TARGET=\"1087368827\"\n\n# Logging helper\nlog() {\n    echo \"[$(date '+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S')] $1\" | tee -a \"$LOG_FILE\"\n}\n\n# Error handler\ndie() {\n    log \"FATAL: $1\"\n    echo \"Error marker\" > \"$DATA_DIR/ERROR-$DATE_STR.marker\"\n    exit 1\n}\n\nlog \"=== Starting Daily Ping v3.0 ===\"\nlog \"Data file: $DATA_FILE\"\n\n# =============================================================================\n# STEP 1: Fetch Bitcoin\n# =============================================================================\nlog \"Fetching Bitcoin from CoinGecko...\"\nBTC_JSON=$(curl -sf --max-time 30 \\\n    \"https://api.coingecko.com/api/v3/simple/price?ids=bitcoin&vs_currencies=usd&include_24hr_change=true\" 2>&1) || {\n    log \"WARNING: Bitcoin fetch failed, will use cached/stale data if available\"\n    BTC_JSON='{}'\n}\n\nBTC_PRICE=$(echo \"$BTC_JSON\" | jq -r '.bitcoin.usd // 0')\nBTC_CHANGE=$(echo \"$BTC_JSON\" | jq -r '.bitcoin.usd_24h_change // 0')\n\nlog \"Bitcoin: \\$$BTC_PRICE (24h: $BTC_CHANGE%)\"\n\n# =============================================================================\n# STEP 2: Fetch Stocks (with retry)\n# =============================================================================\nlog \"Fetching stocks via yfinance...\"\n\nSTOCKS_JSON=$(/opt/venv/bin/python3 << 'PYEOF' 2>&1\nimport yfinance as yf\nimport json\nimport sys\nfrom datetime import datetime\n\nTICKERS = ['NVDA', 'MSFT', 'GOOGL', 'INTC', 'META', 'AMD']\nresults = {}\n\nfor symbol in TICKERS:\n    try:\n        t = yf.Ticker(symbol)\n        info = t.info\n        \n        # Get price\n        current = info.get('currentPrice') or info.get('regularMarketPrice')\n        prev_close = info.get('previousClose')\n        \n        # Calculate change\n        change_pct = info.get('regularMarketChangePercent')\n        if change_pct is None and current and prev_close:\n            change_pct = ((current - prev_close) / prev_close) * 100\n        \n        results[symbol] = {\n            'price': round(current, 2) if current else None,\n            'change_pct': round(change_pct, 2) if change_pct else 0.0,\n            'company': info.get('shortName', symbol)\n        }\n    except Exception as e:\n        results[symbol] = {'error': str(e)}\n\nprint(json.dumps(results, indent=2))\nPYEOF\n) || {\n    log \"ERROR: Stock fetch failed: $STOCKS_JSON\"\n    STOCKS_JSON='{}'\n}\n\n# Validate JSON\nif ! echo \"$STOCKS_JSON\" | jq empty 2>/dev/null; then\n    log \"WARNING: Stock JSON invalid, using empty\"\n    STOCKS_JSON='{}'\nfi\n\nlog \"Stocks fetched: $(echo \"$STOCKS_JSON\" | jq -r 'keys | length') symbols\"\n\n# =============================================================================\n# STEP 3: Fetch Top 10 Trending GitHub Repos\n# =============================================================================\nlog \"Fetching top 10 trending GitHub repos...\"\n\n# Query: created in last ~3 months, sort by stars (velocity indicator)\n# per_page=10 gives us top trending momentum\nDATE_CUTOFF=$(date -d '90 days ago' +%Y-%m-%d)\n\nGH_JSON=$(curl -sf --max-time 30 \\\n    \"https://api.github.com/search/repositories?q=created:>$DATE_CUTOFF&sort=stars&order=desc&per_page=10\" 2>&1) || {\n    log \"WARNING: GitHub fetch failed\"\n    GH_JSON='{\"items\":[]}'\n}\n\n# Validate and extract safely\nif ! echo \"$GH_JSON\" | jq -e '.items' >/dev/null 2>&1; then\n    log \"WARNING: GitHub response invalid, using fallback\"\n    GH_JSON='{\"items\":[]}'\nfi\n\nREPO_COUNT=$(echo \"$GH_JSON\" | jq '.items | length')\nlog \"GitHub: $REPO_COUNT trending repos fetched\"\n\n# =============================================================================\n# STEP 4: Build unified data structure\n# =============================================================================\nlog \"Building unified data structure...\"\n\ncat > \"$DATA_FILE\" << JSONEOF\n{\n  \"meta\": {\n    \"date\": \"$DATE_STR\",\n    \"timestamp\": \"$(date -Iseconds)\",\n    \"version\": \"3.0\"\n  },\n  \"bitcoin\": {\n    \"price\": $BTC_PRICE,\n    \"change_24h_pct\": $BTC_CHANGE\n  },\n  \"stocks\": $STOCKS_JSON,\n  \"github\": $GH_JSON\n}\nJSONEOF\n\nlog \"Data written to: $DATA_FILE ($(stat -c%s \"$DATA_FILE\" 2>/dev/null || echo 0) bytes)\"\n\n# =============================================================================\n# STEP 5: Format and Send\n# =============================================================================\nlog \"Formatting and sending message...\"\n\n/usr/bin/python3 << 'FORMATTER_SCRIPT'\nimport json\nimport sys\nfrom datetime import datetime\nimport subprocess\n\n# Hardcoded target for reliability\nTELEGRAM_TARGET = \"1087368827\"\nDATE_STR = datetime.now().strftime(\"%Y-%m-%d\")\nDATA_FILE = f\"/home/project/openclaw/data/daily-ping-{DATE_STR}.json\"\n\ndef format_stars(count):\n    \"\"\"Format star count to K/M format\"\"\"\n    if count >= 1000000:\n        return f\"{count/1000000:.1f}M\"\n    elif count >= 1000:\n        return f\"{count/1000:.1f}K\"\n    return str(count)\n\ndef main():\n    # Load data\n    try:\n        with open(DATA_FILE, 'r') as f:\n            data = json.load(f)\n    except Exception as e:\n        print(f\"FATAL: Cannot read data file: {e}\", file=sys.stderr)\n        sys.exit(1)\n    \n    meta = data.get('meta', {})\n    btc = data.get('bitcoin', {})\n    stocks = data.get('stocks', {})\n    github = data.get('github', {})\n    repos = github.get('items', [])[:10]  # Top 10\n    \n    # Format Bitcoin\n    btc_price = btc.get('price', 0)\n    btc_change = btc.get('change_24h_pct', 0)\n    btc_arrow = \"📈\" if btc_change >= 0 else \"📉\"\n    btc_sign = \"+\" if btc_change >= 0 else \"\"\n    \n    # Build message\n    lines = [\n        f\"📈 Crypto\",\n        f\"• Bitcoin: ${btc_price:,} ({btc_arrow} {btc_sign}{btc_change:.2f}%)\",\n        \"\",\n        f\"💹 Tech Stocks\",\n    ]\n    \n    # Add stocks\n    for symbol in ['NVDA', 'MSFT', 'GOOGL', 'INTC', 'META', 'AMD']:\n        stock = stocks.get(symbol, {})\n        if 'error' in stock or not stock.get('price'):\n            lines.append(f\"• {symbol} Data unavailable\")\n            continue\n        \n        price = stock.get('price', 0)\n        change = stock.get('change_pct', 0)\n        arrow = \"📈\" if change >= 0 else \"📉\"\n        sign = \"+\" if change >= 0 else \"\"\n        \n        lines.append(f\"• {symbol} ${price:.2f} ({arrow} {sign}{change:.2f}%)\")\n    \n    # Add GitHub repos\n    lines.extend([\"\", \"⭐ Top 10 Trending GitHub Repos\"])\n    \n    for i, repo in enumerate(repos, 1):\n        name = repo.get('name', 'unknown')\n        desc = repo.get('description', '')[:50]  # Truncate\n        stars = repo.get('stargazers_count', 0)\n        \n        if desc:\n            lines.append(f\"{i}. {name} — {desc} ({format_stars(stars)} ⭐)\")\n        else:\n            lines.append(f\"{i}. {name} ({format_stars(stars)} ⭐)\")\n    \n    message = '\\n'.join(lines)\n    \n    # Save debug copy\n    with open(f\"/home/project/openclaw/logs/message-{DATE_STR}.txt\", 'w') as f:\n        f.write(message)\n    \n    print(\"Generated message:\")\n    print(message)\n    print(\"\\n\" + \"=\"*60)\n    \n    # Send via Telegram using OpenClaw CLI\n    try"}},{"type":"text","text":":\\n        # Prepare message - escape newlines"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"moonshotai/kimi-k2.5","usage":{"input":127040,"output":3161,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":130201,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771467361886}}
